5000|$|The {{benefits}} from <b>risk</b> <b>pooling</b> depend {{directly on the}} relative market behavior. This is explained as follows: If we compare two markets and when demand from both markets {{are more or less}} than the average demand, we say that the demands from the market are positively correlated. Thus the benefits derived from <b>risk</b> <b>pooling</b> decreases as the correlation between demands from the two markets becomes more positive.|$|E
